## Personal Background 
I am Arati Poudel. I was born in Gandaki Province in Nepal in the year 2000. I did my undergraduate at the Institute of Agriculture and Animal Science (IAAS), Tribhuvan University, Nepal. My undergraduate research was on horticulture, entitled "Effect of maleic hydrazide and ethrel on performance of cucumber." 

## Research thesis and why this course?
I joined Oklahoma State University (OSU) in Jan 2025 in the Plant and Soil Science department as a master's student. My thesis research topic is "High-throughput Phenotyping for disease prediction in winter wheat" and my advisor is Dr. Alderman. I am taking this 'data science' course, not because my advisor is teaching it, but because I really want to do code on my own, work on my data, interpret the results in the best possible way I can, and do proper analysis once getting acquainted with R packages. For now, let's say to work on my own research data, but actually to feel comfy working with codes and doing their interpretation. 

